Normally I don't like facial
hair, but Spock makes it work.

30
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:08,936
- Hello?
- Sheldon,

31
00:01:09,084 --> 00:01:10,654
it's Dr. Linkletter.

32
00:01:10,739 --> 00:01:13,085
I'm watching Star Trek:
The Original Series.

33
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:15,537
I'm sorry, I'm not up
on my cartoons.

34
00:01:15,622 --> 00:01:17,366
It's not a cartoon.
It's a live-action

35
00:01:17,451 --> 00:01:18,759
science fiction show.

36
00:01:18,910 --> 00:01:20,611
Although there is one called
Star Trek:

37
00:01:20,696 --> 00:01:21,961
The Animated Series.

38
00:01:22,046 --> 00:01:23,529
I believe you.

39
00:01:23,642 --> 00:01:25,795
I was wondering if I can
speak with your mommy.

40
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:27,248
Sure. Hold on.

41
00:01:27,385 --> 00:01:29,716
Mom, Dr. Linkletter's
on the phone.

42
00:01:29,801 --> 00:01:31,397
While we wait,
here's a fun fact.

43
00:01:31,482 --> 00:01:32,810
In the animated series,

44
00:01:32,895 --> 00:01:34,771
Kukulkan was played by
James Doohan.

45
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,006
- Hello?
- James Doohan played Scotty

46
00:01:37,091 --> 00:01:38,400
on Star Trek:
The Original Series.

47
00:01:38,484 --> 00:01:39,997
Sheldon, I've got it.

48
00:01:40,082 --> 00:01:42,610
He tried several accents before
settling on Scottish.

49
00:01:42,695 --> 00:01:44,770
- MARY: Sheldon, hang up.
- SHELDON: Okay.

50
00:01:44,855 --> 00:01:48,020
He felt the Scots were
excellent engineers. Bye.

51
00:01:48,762 --> 00:01:49,795
Dr. Linkletter,

52
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:51,045
<i>what can I do for you?</i>

53
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:53,602
Hello, Mrs. Cooper.
I just wanted to let you know,

54
00:01:53,687 --> 00:01:55,982
with Dr. Sturgis away,
I'll be available

55
00:01:56,067 --> 00:01:57,817
should Sheldon need anything.

56
00:01:57,908 --> 00:02:00,566
Oh, that is very comforting
to know.

57
00:02:00,651 --> 00:02:02,216
Thank you so much.

58
00:02:02,301 --> 00:02:04,403
His well-being is important
to me,

59
00:02:04,716 --> 00:02:07,417
as was made abundantly clear
by my boss.

60
00:02:07,934 --> 00:02:11,317
Okay, well, we are truly
grateful.

61
00:02:11,402 --> 00:02:14,016
Now, I'm not terribly
experienced around children.

62
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:16,181
If he needs to use the restroom,
I don't have to

63
00:02:16,304 --> 00:02:17,887
go in with him, do I?

64
00:02:18,171 --> 00:02:21,364
<i>♪ Nobody else
is stronger than I am ♪</i>

65
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:24,005
<i>♪ Yesterday I moved a mountain</i>

66
00:02:24,090 --> 00:02:26,997
<i>♪ I bet I could be your hero</i>

67
