Pastor Jeff already
covered this.

76
00:02:46,264 --> 00:02:48,269
- He did? - Yeah, we're good.
- Amen.

77
00:02:48,353 --> 00:02:50,663
- Amen.
- Amen.

78
00:02:50,925 --> 00:02:52,511
Can I take your truck tomorrow?

79
00:02:52,603 --> 00:02:54,307
Well, I think you're
riding with me.

80
00:02:54,487 --> 00:02:56,625
Sorry, I'm taking
Missy to school,

81
00:02:56,709 --> 00:02:58,801
and Meemaw's
taking Sheldon.

82
00:02:58,885 --> 00:03:01,325
- Well, can I at least drive?
- Sure.

83
00:03:01,409 --> 00:03:03,307
While you hide in the back
under a tarp?

84
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:05,895
Stop praying for him
and focus on the other two.

85
00:03:06,908 --> 00:03:08,651
Sheldon, good news.

86
00:03:08,736 --> 00:03:10,682
Dr. Linkletter was
calling to say

87
00:03:10,767 --> 00:03:13,534
that while you're at school,
if you need anything,

88
00:03:13,619 --> 00:03:14,884
you can go to him.

89
00:03:15,044 --> 00:03:17,089
Starting college and
you need a babysitter.

90
00:03:17,174 --> 00:03:18,199
That's funny.

91
00:03:18,284 --> 00:03:19,953
I don't need a babysitter.

92
00:03:20,037 --> 00:03:24,174
Dr. Linkletter is just around
in case there's a problem.

93
00:03:24,258 --> 00:03:26,176
- Like if he needs a new diaper?
- Ha!

94
00:03:26,463 --> 00:03:29,050
Enough. Can we please have
a nice dinner?

95
00:03:29,135 --> 00:03:32,026
We could. But you're the one
who wants to eat as a family.

96
00:03:32,111 --> 00:03:34,636
Don't pray for any of 'em.

97
00:03:36,471 --> 00:03:37,480
[knock on door]

98
00:03:37,565 --> 00:03:39,929
- Dr. Linkletter.
- Sheldon.

99
00:03:40,013 --> 00:03:42,160
How wonderfully early it is
to see you.

100
00:03:42,245 --> 00:03:44,605
If you've come by for a snack,
I picked you up

101
00:03:44,690 --> 00:03:46,183
some crackers shaped like fish.

102
00:03:46,268 --> 00:03:47,850
I just wanted to let you know

103
00:03:47,934 --> 00:03:49,461
that I don't need you
to babysit me.

104
00:03:49,545 --> 00:03:51,071
I'm perfectly self-reliant.

105
00:03:51,155 --> 00:03:53,726
Excellent. I'm not very
comfortable around children,

106
00:03:53,810 --> 00:03:55,423
even with your level
of maturity.

107
00:03:55,507 --> 00:03:57,207
How old are you?
Six? Seven?

108
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:58,409
Eleven.

109
00:03:58,541 --> 00:03:59,818
I see.

110
00:03:59,903 --> 00:04:01,603
Then it's good I kept
the receipt for this

111
00:04:01,687 --> 00:04:04,065
bottle of bubbles
shaped like a bear.

112
00:04:04,807 --> 00:04:06,129
I should get going.

113
00:04:06,213 --> 00:04:08,610
My philosophy class starts
in a few minutes.

114
00:04:08,694 --> 00:04:11,874
Ah, yes, the great thinkers.
Socrates, Plato.

115
00:04:11,958 --> 00:04:16,182
Speaking of which,
I got you some Play-Doh.

116
00:04:21,056 --> 00:04:23,058
I figure you don't
want me to walk you in?

117
00:04:23,143 --> 00:04:24,452
I've trained you well.

118
00:04:24,893 --> 00:04:27,281
Do you have everything
you need? Lunch money?

119
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:29,027
- Yep.
- Locker combination?

120
00:04:29,112 --> 00:04:30,346
Right here.

121
00:04:30,567 --> 00:04:33,432
- Why is it there?
- Writing on my hand is so fifth grade.

122
00:04:33,581 --> 00:04:34,963
Of course.

123
00:04:35,564 --> 00:04:37,450
Okay, I'm gonna go in.

124
00:04:38,596 --> 00:04:40,190
I assume you don't
want a hug?

125
00:04:40,354 --> 00:04:42,139
Make it quick.

126
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:45,764
- That's enough.
- Okay.

127
00:04:46,847 --> 00:04:49,299
- Wish me luck.
- Good luck.

